	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">General news posts from Gordon</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=190753" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000017.html">Don't post anything serious yet... still testing</a></B><P>

And its still broken.. Chat handles are showing now but THE LOG IN PAGE IS NOT SECURE<P>

<B>The login page, or rather the frame in which login takes place, is secure. Right-click in the window, choose properties, and you will see that it is secure.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000133.html">problems with multiple accounts/servers/computers and their solutions</a></B><P>

The problem is that the file/entries used for storing friends lists, hotkey bindings, social configurations and skill settings are stored locally on your machine with no differentiation of server or account.<P>

Solution: wherever this data is kept for the character "bob" have the entry for that data include the server name.<P>

<B>These are certainly some good suggestions. We have hopes in the near future for some updates to the client that we've been planning for a while. We'll see about getting this on the list.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000159.html">Message Board Security - Cookies</a></B><P>

I am now being automatically authenticated, even though I did not check "Save Password".<P>

<B>If you close your browser, and reopen it, it will kill the current session and establish a new one. Once you've logged in in a particular browser window, you are basically authenticated until you close that window.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000256.html">Tired of total lack of courtesy</a></B><P>

Verant PLEASE, this is not good business and its downright messed up. Give players time to get to a safe spot. AT the minium players should have 5 minutes to log out. 10 - 15 being a more appropriate time<P>

<B>There is supposed to be at least a 5 minute warning in all cases of an intentional server downing. Of course, it is possible that some of the notifications are missed due to zoning or fighting. at the time that the warning messages are sent. Others might log in after a message and feel that they weren't given a warning. I myself have sat on a server and watched warnings be issued every minute for 5 minutes, only to go into the chat-server and hear from people who didn't see the warning.<P>

That said, if it's apparent that at least 5 minutes warning isn't given in the case of an outage, please let us know what server the problem occurred on so that we can take steps to ensure that proper warning is given in the future.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000274.html">What about servers with different xp tables to set different challenge levels?</a></B><P>

What if Verant were to set up a different set of servers with lower XP tables?<P>

<B>Hello Flasherz,<P>

This issue is addressed in section 4.3 of the forum FAQ at <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html">everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html</a><P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000352.html">One suggestion and one problem</a></B><P>

I would like to propose that container windows have their "clickable" area changed to just the top of the window. This issue presents itself most prominently when attempting trade skills. Moving items quickly between containers often causes a hit on the bars seperating the slots of the container, which causes you to pick the container window up.<P>

Now my problem. I use the Dvorak keyboard layout, and a Verant-created keyboard.txt file for Dvorak was not presented with the various international keyboard layouts that were recently released. I modified the keyboard.txt file to reflect my layout, but have a couple of issues. First off, outside of using the keyboard to talk, the keys are not remapped. I still have to use the QWERTY slash (/) key (which is my 'z' key) to open the chat bar. <P>

<B>Thanks for the note regarding Dvorak keyboard layouts and the problems you've experienced. I'll forward the post to the client programmers to see if they have an idea on how to address the issue.<P>

Oh, and regarding containers, we're planning on some updates to the UI in the near future. I'll mention your suggestion to the people who are working on it.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000376.html">Omg! I cant connect!</a></B><P>

anyone else have this problem? Its starting to make me mad..... <P>

<B>That's strange. I'll ask the board programmer to take a look at it.</B><P>

heh, boards bugged. by replying to threads from the west coast, you will actually knock them back a few pages. same goes for new ones you start, they will be 2 or 3 pages back.<P>

<B>Oh, ok, this makes sense. The boards were switched over to west coast time last night. They were previously on east coast time. When the change was made, all posts started coming in three hours earlier than they used to. <P>

It should have worked itself out by now.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000382.html">My name?!</a></B><P>

This board is telling me that my name is "Kearlie", and posting that as the author of a post...<P>

My name is actually "Kearlie_VoF". <P>

<B>If you added the "_VoF" in the last 24 hours, there's a good chance that it hasn't been updated in the boards login DB. I'd recommend that you try again later.<P>

-Gordon</b><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000396.html">Spelling Error on Some Items</a></B><P>

There is a spelling error on some items, such as "A Gigantic Zweihander," that use the word "Zweihander." Zwei is a German word meaning "two," so the rest of the word should be in German also, making it "Zweihaender" (Since I don't think EQ supports umlauts - i.e., "Zweihänder"). It's only a small problem, but it is kind of annoying. Another solution would be to just make it "A Gigantic Two-hander."<P>

<B>I'd like to thank you both for posting your thoughts and historical knowledge. The breadth and diversity of knowledge possessed across the EverQuest player-base is quite astounding. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000398.html">/who GUILD all and /roleplay</a></B><P>

Well, I dont know if anyone noticed, but unlike the patch msg announced, people who are in /roleplay do NOT show up on /who GUILD all. I dont want to sound offensive, but maybe you guys should double or triple check patch content to make sure everything is there?<P>

<B>Yeah, you have a point :( I sincerely apologize for announcing a patch change that didn't take place. As it turns out, one file necessary for the /who all "guild" to work on /roleplayers wasn't included in the patch package. It will be in the next one.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000654.html">What do Uber and VAK stand for?</a></B><p>

just wondering...<P>

<B>This might be a good time to mention that "VAK" is a derogatory term, falling under the umbrella of "namecalling", that isn't allowed on the boards any longer.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000662.html">Please welcome Cindy Archuleta!</a></B><P>

<I>Hello all,<P>

We're pleased to announced that Cindy Archuleta has joined the Verant Team. Cindy is a former Guide, and was also the coordinator for the St. Louis and Las Vegas EQ Gatherings. <P>

Cindy will be coordinating future gatherings for EQ and other Verant products, and will also be here on the boards, helping to moderate the forums and answer questions from time to time. We definately look forward to Cindy's (who will be posting as "Abigale_") assistance in all of these areas and hearitly welcome her to the team. <P>

Please join me in giving her a warm welcome. <P>

-Gordon</I>
</blockquote>
